text.tspan: Change in maternal mortality ratio, 1990 to 2015
Maternal mortality ratio is the number of women who die from pregnancy-related causes while pregnant or within 42 days of pregnancy
termination per 100,000 live births. This is given as the relative change in ratio from 1990 to 2015.
